title: FSX BDOaviation-WIII Soekarno-Hatta
description:
Soekarno-Hatta International Airport is the main airport serving the greater Jakarta area on the island of Java, Indonesia. The airport is named after the first president of Indonesia, Soekarno, and the first vice-president, Mohammad Hatta. Located about 20km west of Jakarta, in Tangerang, Banten. Soekarno-Hatta airport began to operate in 1985.
